text: Not yet. But I really think I should as it comes with various benefits - one of them like you said - 'a break from exams' hahaha I am looking forward to that one.

Do you think there's an advantage into getting your university application in early? 

Will you be more likely to secure a place?

I don't think that it makes much of a difference, if it makes any difference at all. I think they probably just look at all the applications received by the deadline. It's good to get it done to avoid the stress of applying last minute, but i think that is probably the only benefit
